retraction: third-party services and data provenance
=====================================================

The 'retraction' R package is licensed under GPL-3 (see the LICENSE file).
It queries external services and data sources at run time. The package code
is independent of these services; the notes below describe the terms that
govern the data they return, which users are responsible for observing.

XeraRetractionTracker (default source)
--------------------------------------
Base URL: https://openscience.xera.ac/retractions/api/v1/
Serves the Retraction Watch database. No authentication is required for read
access. Retraction Watch data is made openly available by The Center for
Scientific Integrity through Crossref
(https://gitlab.com/crossref/retraction-watch-data). Users who redistribute
bulk downloads should review the current Retraction Watch and Crossref terms.

Crossref (optional source)
--------------------------
Base URL: https://api.crossref.org/
Crossref metadata is openly available. The package sends an optional "mailto"
value to use the polite request pool, as Crossref recommends.

OpenAlex (optional source)
--------------------------
Base URL: https://api.openalex.org/
The OpenAlex dataset is released under CC0. The "is_retracted" flag it exposes
is derived from the Retraction Watch database.

No third-party code is bundled in this package.
